Temprith Ilistar was the sixth King of the Ilistar Dynasty who ruled the city-state of Westgate.
Temprith became the next King of Westgate by seizing the throne from his nephew Farnath III upon the death of King Farnath II in the . He would only rule for a few years until he was overthrown and killed by his cousin Thartryn II in the .
